{"passages": [{"text": "Introversion is an orientation toward the internal private world of one’s self and one’s inner thoughts and feelings, rather than toward the outer world of people and things.\nIntroverts are relatively more withdrawn, retiring, reserved, quiet, and deliberate; they may tend to mute or guard expression of positive affect, adopt more skeptical views or positions, and prefer to work independently.", "chunk_number": 0}],
            "final_answer": "Introverts are oriented toward their internal private world of self, thoughts, and feelings, and are relatively more withdrawn, retiring, reserved, quiet, and deliberate. They may mute positive affect, adopt skeptical views, and prefer independent work. Extraverts, on the other hand, orient their interests and energies toward the outer world of people and things, and are relatively outgoing, gregarious, sociable, and openly expressive."
